        content: 'Missouri does not mandate paid sick leave, paid family leave, or state disability insurance for private employers. Federal FMLA applies to employers with 50 or more employees. Missouri has a state continuation coverage law that provides up to nine months of continuation coverage for employees of businesses with fewer than 20 workers.\n\nMissouri\'s small group market follows ACA standards for employers with 2 to 50 employees. The state approved Medicaid expansion through a voter-initiated ballot measure, extending coverage to adults earning up to 138 percent of the federal poverty level. This expansion reduced the uninsured rate and affects employer coverage strategy for lower-wage positions. Missouri has not enacted a state retirement savings mandate, though discussions have occurred.'
